Key Match Events: Dennis Schroder scored a clutch layup to cap off the Nets' night at 106 points
Cameron Johnson was blocked with seconds to go, preventing the Grizzlies from winning
Post-Match Reflections: The biggest positive for the Nets was the balanced scoring, showcasing the team's chemistry and coaching
Miscellaneous Highlights: Brooklyn's veterans have emerged as some of the best role players in the NBA
Others: Dorian Finney-Smith was the team's third-leading scorer with 17 points on 6-of-10 shooting
Johnson matched Schroder with 20 points of his own on 8-of-11 shooting
